msgid "Tutorial: Baran"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: Two_Brothers_With_A_Third_Difficulty/scenarios/04_Return_to_the_Village.cfg:226
msgid "Baran is now free for you to use to his full potential! Baran is a <i>Red Mage</i>. He is unique among your units in that he has a <i>neutral</i> alignment. He has a strong ranged attack in which he hurls powerful magical fireballs at enemies. Unfortunately, the enemies against which these fireballs are strongest (undead and wood-based enemies) aren't available here at the end of this campaign for you to fry. Baran can also do a weak melee attack with his staff, dealing <i>impact</i> damage to enemies."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=second_unit
#: Two_Brothers_With_A_Third_Difficulty/scenarios/04_Return_to_the_Village.cfg:242
msgid "We’re almost there!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Baran
#: Two_Brothers_With_A_Third_Difficulty/scenarios/04_Return_to_the_Village.cfg:247
msgid "That warlord! It’s..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Arvith
#: Two_Brothers_With_A_Third_Difficulty/scenarios/04_Return_to_the_Village.cfg:252
msgid "Yes, I’d know that face anywhere. Especially after what you did to it."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Baran
#: Two_Brothers_With_A_Third_Difficulty/scenarios/04_Return_to_the_Village.cfg:257
msgid "The warlord from Toen Caric."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Tairach
#: Two_Brothers_With_A_Third_Difficulty/scenarios/04_Return_to_the_Village.cfg:262
msgid "You! The mage who scarred me with fire! KILL THEM!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Baran
#: Two_Brothers_With_A_Third_Difficulty/scenarios/04_Return_to_the_Village.cfg:267
msgid "Let’s finish what we started, brother."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Arvith
#: Two_Brothers_With_A_Third_Difficulty/scenarios/04_Return_to_the_Village.cfg:272
msgid "Aye. I’ll be the right arm, and you’ll be the left. Let’s go!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=second_unit
#: Two_Brothers_With_A_Third_Difficulty/scenarios/04_Return_to_the_Village.cfg:311
msgid "Hey look! It's Reeve Hoban!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=second_unit
#: Two_Brothers_With_A_Third_Difficulty/scenarios/04_Return_to_the_Village.cfg:317
msgid "One of Reeve Hoban's men!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: Two_Brothers_With_A_Third_Difficulty/scenarios/04_Return_to_the_Village.cfg:322
msgid "Hey Reeve! Look who showed up!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Reeve Hoban
#. Reeve starts to say "Arvith" but then interrupts himself:
#: Two_Brothers_With_A_Third_Difficulty/scenarios/04_Return_to_the_Village.cfg:364
msgid "Hello Arv-wait, what's this? Why do you have a dark mage with you, Arvith?!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Arvith
#: Two_Brothers_With_A_Third_Difficulty/scenarios/04_Return_to_the_Village.cfg:368
msgid "Hold, fair Reeve. This mage agreed to fight alongside me after I spared his life."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Reeve Hoban
#: Two_Brothers_With_A_Third_Difficulty/scenarios/04_Return_to_the_Village.cfg:372
msgid "Well, if you trust him, I guess that I can do so, as well. Anyways, I am glad that you have returned."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Reeve Hoban
#: Two_Brothers_With_A_Third_Difficulty/scenarios/04_Return_to_the_Village.cfg:379
msgid "I am glad to see you returned."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Baran
#: Two_Brothers_With_A_Third_Difficulty/scenarios/04_Return_to_the_Village.cfg:386
msgid "No gladder than I am to be here. But what has happened to Maghre?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Reeve Hoban
#: Two_Brothers_With_A_Third_Difficulty/scenarios/04_Return_to_the_Village.cfg:391
msgid "Soon after you departed we were beset by orcs. With half the men of Maghre gone, we could not stop them."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Reeve Hoban
#: Two_Brothers_With_A_Third_Difficulty/scenarios/04_Return_to_the_Village.cfg:396
msgid "The orcish warlord aims to enslave us. We will not be able to hold out for much longer."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Reeve Hoban
#: Two_Brothers_With_A_Third_Difficulty/scenarios/04_Return_to_the_Village.cfg:401
msgid "Have a care, his men are fell fighters and have killed many. Very few remain who can bear arms, but I will send them to aid you in battle."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Reeve Hoban
#: Two_Brothers_With_A_Third_Difficulty/scenarios/04_Return_to_the_Village.cfg:425
msgid "Ungh... My time has come... Arvith... Baran... the defense of Maghre now falls to the two of you..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Arvith
#: Two_Brothers_With_A_Third_Difficulty/scenarios/04_Return_to_the_Village.cfg:430
msgid "No! Reeve!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Baran
#: Two_Brothers_With_A_Third_Difficulty/scenarios/04_Return_to_the_Village.cfg:435
msgid "You orcs will pay for this!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Arvith
#: Two_Brothers_With_A_Third_Difficulty/scenarios/04_Return_to_the_Village.cfg:447
msgid "...well, we can't sit around mourning Reeve while we are still beset by orcs... To the defense of Maghre, men!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Baran
#: Two_Brothers_With_A_Third_Difficulty/scenarios/04_Return_to_the_Village.cfg:452
msgid "Maybe we can take up his position for him?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Arvith
#: Two_Brothers_With_A_Third_Difficulty/scenarios/04_Return_to_the_Village.cfg:457
msgid "We shall see!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Reeve Hoban
#: Two_Brothers_With_A_Third_Difficulty/scenarios/04_Return_to_the_Village.cfg:477
msgid "Here, have some gold. You could probably put it to better use than I can."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Arvith
#: Two_Brothers_With_A_Third_Difficulty/scenarios/04_Return_to_the_Village.cfg:483
msgid "It appears Reeve left behind some gold in his keep!"
msgstr ""

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: Two_Brothers_With_A_Third_Difficulty/scenarios/04_Return_to_the_Village.cfg:507
msgid "Slay the Orcish Warlord to free the village"
msgstr ""

#. [objectives]
#: Two_Brothers_With_A_Third_Difficulty/scenarios/04_Return_to_the_Village.cfg:523
msgid "You can use Reeve Hoban’s keep to recruit or recall additional units."
msgstr ""

#. [objectives]
#: Two_Brothers_With_A_Third_Difficulty/scenarios/04_Return_to_the_Village.cfg:526
msgid "Have Arvith make use of Reeve Hoban’s keep."
msgstr ""

#. [objectives]
#: Two_Brothers_With_A_Third_Difficulty/scenarios/04_Return_to_the_Village.cfg:529
msgid "Use Reeve Hoban’s keep."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Tairach
#: Two_Brothers_With_A_Third_Difficulty/scenarios/04_Return_to_the_Village.cfg:570
msgid "Today, you shall pay for disfiguring my face, mage!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Baran
#: Two_Brothers_With_A_Third_Difficulty/scenarios/04_Return_to_the_Village.cfg:575
msgid "I have already paid with the lives of my men at Toen Caric. It is time I righted that mistake and finished this once and for all."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Tairach
#: Two_Brothers_With_A_Third_Difficulty/scenarios/04_Return_to_the_Village.cfg:615
msgid "You again!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Arvith
#: Two_Brothers_With_A_Third_Difficulty/scenarios/04_Return_to_the_Village.cfg:620
msgid "It is time for me to finish what Baran started!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Tairach
#: Two_Brothers_With_A_Third_Difficulty/scenarios/04_Return_to_the_Village.cfg:660
msgid "Hey wait, weren't you one of that insignificant mage Rotharik's men? Weren't you supposed to be capturing Baran and bringing him to me?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Muff Toras
#: Two_Brothers_With_A_Third_Difficulty/scenarios/04_Return_to_the_Village.cfg:665
msgid "Yes, that was originally the plan. However, I've changed my mind: I'd much rather kill you instead!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Arvith
#: Two_Brothers_With_A_Third_Difficulty/scenarios/04_Return_to_the_Village.cfg:681
msgid "It is finished. We’ve defeated him at last. It was good to have you at my side, Baran."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Baran
#: Two_Brothers_With_A_Third_Difficulty/scenarios/04_Return_to_the_Village.cfg:686
msgid "So much has been destroyed. It will be difficult to repair all that the orcs and undead have wrecked. And they could come again."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Arvith
#: Two_Brothers_With_A_Third_Difficulty/scenarios/04_Return_to_the_Village.cfg:691
msgid "I must go back to earning my living. But we have our amulets, little brother. If you are beset again, I will come."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Arvith
#: Two_Brothers_With_A_Third_Difficulty/scenarios/04_Return_to_the_Village.cfg:709
msgid "I don’t think we can rescue anyone from these villages. It is too late."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Baran
#: Two_Brothers_With_A_Third_Difficulty/scenarios/04_Return_to_the_Village.cfg:714
msgid "I was too weak to protect these people. Oh, why did this happen to me?!"
msgstr ""

#. [scenario]: id=02_The_Chase
#: Two_Brothers_With_A_Third_Difficulty/scenarios/02_The_Chase.cfg:5
msgid "The Chase"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: Two_Brothers_With_A_Third_Difficulty/scenarios/02_The_Chase.cfg:23
msgid "Arvith and his band rode north in search of his missing brother."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: Two_Brothers_With_A_Third_Difficulty/scenarios/02_The_Chase.cfg:30
msgid ""
"16 V, 363 YW\n"
"Excerpt from the journal of Arvith of Maghre\n"
"\n"
"We’ve been searching three days for Baran, and turned up nothing. My best hunch was to head north into the borderlands, where the necromancer’s minions could safely hide; everywhere else is more farmland. At first I thought the search might be useless, but late in the first day we found a set of tracks. Some of them had been made by skeletal feet.\n"
"\n"
"We’re close enough to be certain now: those tracks are heading into the Grey Woods. No one from Maghre or any of the other villages has gone into that forest in living memory. Stories have been passed down for generations warning against it. Supposedly the place is haunted by lost souls who hunger for the living, and anyone who dies there is doomed to join them."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: Two_Brothers_With_A_Third_Difficulty/scenarios/02_The_Chase.cfg:39
msgid ""
"16 V, 363 YW\n"
"Excerpt from the journal of Arvith of Maghre\n"
"\n"
"But I’m past superstitions now; I’ve seen enough of the world to guess at the truth behind these sorts of tales. The forest is home to elves — unfriendly ones, if the stories have any basis at all. I worry for my men; horses don’t fight well in forests, and the elves will be more dangerous in their own territory. But there are things that need done and questions that need answered. Something bigger is happening. One necromancer terrorizing townsfolk is nothing new, but why didn’t his servants scatter when he was killed? Where are they headed now? And most importantly, why did they take Baran with them?\n"
"\n"
"Besides... I want my brother back."
msgstr ""

